Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top for 4 servings) and preheat
#oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon},
@Fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt
and pepper. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{} (for 4 servings, spread out
across entire sheet).

Evenly brush tops of chicken cutlets with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Mound
coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere. Roast on middle rack for
~{5%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Toss green beans on opposite side of baking sheet from chicken with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss green beans on
a second sheet.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is crispy and cooked through and green beans
are tender and lightly browned at the edges, ~{12-15%minutes}.
(For 4, roast chicken on middle rack and green beans on top rack.)

> Green beans may finish before chicken—if so, remove from oven and continue
> roasting chicken.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise. When chicken has 5 minutes left,
toast baguette in oven or #toaster oven{} until lightly golden.

Spread cut sides of baguette with @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide chicken, green beans, and garlic bread between plates. Serve.